Steven Johnsons Syndrome (A) is autoimmune and not drug-related. Acute Generalized Exanthematous Pustulosis (B) typically involves infections or immunodeficiencies rather than medication reactions. Morbilliform eruption (D) also aligns with infections or immunosuppression. The recent medication change and hypersensitivity skin reactions strongly suggest drug-induced hypersensitivity syndrome (C).

